I am ashamed when I am not prepared in a subject and I have to 
answer in the presence of the patients.

I feel guilty when I should have done something at any rate but I 
haven't done it.

I experienced it when I was accepted at the Medical Higher 
Institute.
I felt it when I sat for my exam in anatomy.

I experience that feeling when I am unsulted without deserving 
it or when someone deceives me.
When my grandfather died.
I feel disgusted with toadies, hypocrites, chameleons.
When I do something unworthy.
When I offended my parents without wanting it.
After each successfully passed exam I am happy.

A friend of mine gave birth to a child. Very dangerous delivery. 
I was afraid for her and for the baby.

I get angry when someone imputes on me things I never can do, 
naturally negative. Servility, "connections", impudence, traits 
that get me mad.

My brother is a soldier. He promised to come home in a furlough 
but in the last moment he phoned and said that he could not come.
I am disgusted with liers, hypocrites, slanderers, flunkeys.

Recently I saw a young girl fawning on a man. And what for - 
money and things. I was ashamed to be a woman.
When I have been overhastingly offending or hurting.

After the term exams I happened to meet a person that I respect 
and of whom I think very highly. It was nice that although we see 
each other rarely he had not forgotten me.

Few years ago my father was very ill. He stayed at a hospital for 
a long time. Then I experienced that terrible feeling that I 
might lose him.

I have a friend that I deeply trusted but it happened that I lost 
my confidence in her for which she herself was to blame.

We are several friends but our characters are very different and 
we inevitably split in the two extremes. It is sad that I myself 
don't know what to do, I try not to hurt either of the "parties" 
because there are conflicts to which one I should belong.

I stayed for several weeks with a friend of mine before she moved 
to live with her husband. One evening he came drunk and made an 
awful scene, which I still remember.

In the past I experienced this feeling almost all the time - 
wherever I went, in different sutuations. I was small and I had 
to be taken to kindergarten, but me the fool didn't dare to tell 
exactly where, finally as a result I was late.

My roommate got married and invited me to share a flat with them. 
But with a young couple there should not be a third person. I am 
to blame for not following the advise of the others, but it is 
not late still.

I experienced this feeling when I was accepted as a student. 
Because everything turned out different from my expectations. 
Although I passed the exam successfully I was accepted as a 
student only when I didn't expect it at all, namely at the 
beginning of September.

In the real sense of the word I experienced fear in my first 
months in the army. During my first night of duty. The cause for 
all this was a bear. I became panic sticken (may be for the first 
time) and even forgot that I had a gun.

When I was a soldier I quarrelled with my commander and may be in 
revenge for this he detailed me on duty two successive nights. 
Naturally he checked me up on the second night and found me 
asleep for which he sent me to the cells.

Sometimes I experience sadness for the Sports High School and for 
my unrealized dreams in the sport. Anyway there I spent six years 
of my life.

Sort of awkward. I'd introduced (a lover) but introduced as a 
friend to some members of my family, and my niece Yavanna who's 
six was home from school and at Mum's and Dad's and was really 
silly and at first it was ok, but it went on and on - yukky pooh! 
You eat your snot, etc. and I felt cross she wouldn't stop. But 
she had an audience and was in one of those moods. Once I'd 
accepted it was something everyone does at time I felt better - 
it was partly having my friend there.

In my 20s - and was going out to dinner to celebrate a friend's 
birthday. Her (older - in 30s) cousin, really wanted me to get 
drunk cos I'd visited their (cousin & wife) place quite a bit, 
but had always been very careful - brought up to believe in 
moderation in drink (but not guilt repression etc). I mixed 
drinking with smoking (which I rarely did) and got drunk and had 
to leave the table to get sick in the loo, and later went home 
and was sick again; have never felt so awful in my life. And I 
didn't want to face or tell my other flatmates, or family.

I used to pinch change from my father's mantlepiece (never my 
mother - she didn't get enough housekeeping) and then I'd feel 
when we went to church as a family I'd felt awkward cos I felt 
I'm expected to go to communion and I would but I was afraid and 
guilty 'cos I committed a mortal sin.
Spontaneous picnic with sister and friend and children - great.
Can think of no time that I have felt fear.

Teenage neighbours smashed my letterbox for the fifth time in a 
couple of months. It was a deliberate action of kids who had 
stayed in my home, had meals there yet took a dislike to my 
daughter.
Guy I cared for went back to Canada to live.

Bus driver driving roughly - old man fell off seat into aisle - 
driver wouldn't stop - disgusted with her behaviour.

A daughter in court for staff pilfering, she was dressed like a 
"street walker" - I had a friend form overseas with me and was 
falsely trying to impress with my family.

Reported neighbour to police for taking to my daughter with 
baseball ball - her counsellor rang me and after long talk 
convinced me the woman was o.k. I felt guilty for ringing the 
police then guilty for feeling guilty about it.

Meeting with two of my friends I had not seen for 15 years. They 
were special people to me.

I was in the Korean War. We were attacked with mortars, me and 
companion. We stopped the jeep and ran for cover. Fortunately 
neither of us was hit but we both came close to being killed.

I've a situation of responsibility an employee who had a habit of 
being late, came late again after promising to say he would be at 
work in a few minutes, then arrived 3 hours later. He had been 
drinking.

My brother in law was dying of cancer. To see him wasting away 
was very sad.
Disgust at myself when I stroked a sleeping girl's private parts.

My son was apprehended for shoplifting at the age of 14. Because 
I too had been apprehended at the same age I felt the shame of 
not having been able to prevent my son from acting in the same 
way.

I removed an article of clothing belonging to my employer while 
in a position of trust.

When we took out an 84 year old woman for the evening and had 
hamburgers. She described the evening out as her happiest night 
out in 20 years.

While tramping on a narrow path two of us were confronted by a 
woman with two snarling dogs, demanding we get off the property - 
via a flooded river !

A friend got angry and drove "like a lunatic" with me and others 
in his car. I was angry about his dangerous driving.

A boy I look after for the probation service deliberately 
offended to provoke a reaction from the police.

4-letter words on a TV programme (Roche) while we were 
entertaining "conservative" relations who wanted to see the first 
episode.

A young visitor to the house stole money from an elderly 
visitor's purse. It wasn't noticed for some hours.

I had to leave an important function early because of family 
commitments. Someone else had to complete my job.

I was seriously injured in a road accident. The very first steps 
I took with only one crutch to support me I felt so good. I enjoy 
being alive.

I was attacked, standing in a doorway, by a pack of 5 dogs, 
alsatians and farm dogs with my escape route blocked by a shut 
fence.

In the house where I live there is a new flatmate. His friends 
unfortunately are the dirt of society, intelligent, fashonable, 
rich and bored. At a party recently they were doing things I 
didn't like done in my house. I felt angry at them.

I was driving near my girlfriend's house and I decided to keep 
going because it was late and I would be back in the next few 
days anyway. The next day she was killed in a road accident.

My girlfriend came home after a business dinner at the most 
expensive place in town drunk as a skunk. Whats more she drove 
home and couldn't remember doing so. I was disgusted by her state 
and her actions.

A good friend of mine told me in comfidence that once he had 
tried to commit suicide. To meet him you wouldn't think so. I 
told another friend of mine about this when she was feeling 
depressed about her twin brother's suicide. I broke a bond of 
confidentiality.

When I was young I stole something from a shop and got caught, 
then I was taken to the police station and my parents had to come 
and get me.

When I found out that a set task (i.e. 2 essays and a test), the 
thought of which had oppressed me, were not on the date I had 
thought.
When confronted and in my opinion hassled by the police.

Disgust - no. Maybe it is more precise to say revultion at a worm 
or a snake. But I mean it in a social aspect when somebody had 
behaved like a scoundrel to you, when by his actions he has made 
you change your attitude towards him but I thing this feeling the 
way I meant it, is not typical for the people interrelations.

When you betray the trust you have been given. This is connected 
with copying at a class-work at school.

When I have forgotten to warn somebody for something, or when I 
have forgotten to bring something I have been asked for.

When, for example, I was in my eleventh school year and I learned 
I had been classed for the Bulgarian Language and Literature 
National Olympiad.

When, for example, my grandfather fell seriously ill. It was 
necessary for him to be operated and I felt great fear of losing 
him because he is so dear to me.

When, for example, I was not approved to continue my studies at 
the Moscow University, no matter that I had the highest marks and 
in general the best records of all the candidates.

When, for example, I left for the first time my parents and I 
went to live in Sofia.
When, for example, someone is calumnating.
When, for example, I fail in my undertakings.

For example, when I have promised something but I haven't 
fulfilled it.

Some time ago a close relative of mine got off cheap with the 
worst.
The last time I felt it was when I was coming home late at night.
I haven't often felt this feeling. Once someone stole my garment.
Recently I happened to remain alone for a long time.

I don't remember about a situation when I have experienced this 
feeling. Maybe it was when I saw a drunkard in the street.
I lied to my best friend and I wouldn't reform what I had done.
It happens to me quite often. I can't describe a particular case.

Realizing one's desire, an experienced feeling of satisfaction 
from the realization of one's desires and aims.

Fear of the loss of a close friend, of feeling the ground slipping 
from under my feet.

Attitude to some manners of dealing and some "sanctioned" 
relations.

Feeling unable to preserve one's ideas and ambitions as innocent 
as they are when you are young.
Attitude to a related family.

Exaggerating certain circumstances, wrong attitude and evaluation 
of these circumstances.
Low evaluation of other people's cares.
I won a sport contest.
If a close relative's life is in danger.
A close person lied to me.
Getting separated from my girlfriend.
Encouter with a prostitute.
A theft committed by me.
Lack of respect for my parents.
When my son was born.
Before an examination.
Unjust punishment of a friend of mine.
After the loss of a close relative.

When somebody behaves like a scoundrel. Recently a colleague of 
mine used the name of another one for his own benefit.

I travelled on a bus and I forgot to punch the ticket. A ticket 
collector came in and I had to pay the fine. I did it with a feeling 
of shame.
I forgot to convey an important announcement.
Meeting a loved man.

I felt a physical fear, if I can call it this way, today, in the bus where 
I was sitting on the first seat. While turning the driver didn't 
see the tram which was making a dash towards us (coming from the 
side I was), and whose driver intended to cross in yellow 
light.

At an unjust, or to be more precise, at a bureaucratic treatment 
of one's personality.
When one is alone and knows that all the others are celebrating.
At the sight of an insect, such as the black-beetle.

When not fulfilling any of my obligations to a person whom I 
respect.

When something unpleasant happens to a friend or relative of 
yours and you are at the bottom of it.

I sensed such a feeling when I understood I was admitted to the 
University. I was at home, the atmosphere was still, though I 
myself was full of suspense. I tried to do different things. When 
the telephone rang and...! Yes, of course there were other 
situations when I felt a similar feeling but I was unmindful of 
them.

This feeling I sensed quite recently. It was arisen by the 
terrific thought that I might lose the man I loved !

Anger I felt when my boyfriend told me he didn't mind breaking it 
off with me, i.e. each of us to take his own road. Because until 
that moment, he deliberately restricted our dates. The motives 
were brought to my knowledge later.

Sometimes, when I'm alone I am seized by this feeling. But it 
always helps me to come round and at the same time to judge if it 
is worth. Very often this feeling is caused to me by people - 
friends who I love and respect.

Such a feeling springs up in me sometimes when I have meals at a 
catering establishment. It is a result either of the look of the 
food or when watching the way some people eat.
This happens to me when I am not prepared in a given subject.

Quite unconsciously I offended a girlfriend of mine. It was 
really worthy to pass this fact over in silence, but I acted so, 
because I believed I was right. In fact it often happens to me to 
feel guilt, after I have already done the deed.
When I was admitted to the University.

I had to have my tonsils out. I had been making up my mind almost 
for a year - I was afraid. But during the two hours in the 
hospital room, while I was waiting to be called for the operation I 
felt a real fear - of the pain, of what they were going to do to 
me, of the unknown.

In a conversation my boyfriend expressed definite and quite 
pretentious opinions and he took up an attitude towards a theory 
which he himself had never known. His information was from 
fortuitous sources.

Summer, heavy rain, storm - I was standing with my face stick to 
the window: the childhood, something was going away forever this 
summer, I was leaving my home, I was going to study in another 
town, for the first time I was leaving my parents, friends, I had 
to manage myself, a long and loved period of my life was over - I 
was crying.
I saw in the street a man spitting.

I talked with a man who stammered and without controlling myself, 
I started to talk imitating him.
Always, and this happens often when I do not keep my word.
When I understood that I was admitted to the University.

I felt this feeling when one day my landlord's cat had crept 
under my bed and I couldn't cope with it during an hour and a 
half.

I feel this feeling when I am to fill in a questionnaire or a 
form.
When the man I loved decided to leave me forever.

I have felt this feeling when a person whom I believe and respect, 
lied to me.

I feel shame when sometimes, (unconsciously) I behave unethically 
and without understanding the problems of the man I love.
When I offend somebody unfairly.

A quarrel was followed by the decision of leaving a person close 
to me. Several days later my regret was great. I was beside 
myself. Quite unexpectedly he came and the conflict was calmly 
solved. I was glad at the possibility to be with him.

One evening I was watching the news on TV. Again they were 
talking about the danger of war. Suddenly I imagined what it 
might mean for me, for my friends, for the people close to me. I 
felt it a very near and possible event.

Unfair and unjust attitude toward a person close to me, what I 
was the witness of, caused anger in me.

The thought that I'll never sit at the school desk again, caused 
a deep grief at the end of my eleventh form.

I felt disgust with a person whose behaviour was out of the 
elementary human norms.

I had not punched a ticket in the bus because I had a card. But 
when the ticket-collector came it turned out that I had forgotten 
it. The shame I felt was great though it was not done on purpose.

At a moment of affect I offended a person very close to me. He 
had given me ground for that but it was a trifling in comparison 
with the way I insulted him. A moment later I felt a sense of 
guilt.
When I understood I was admitted to the Sofia University.

I broke my knee when I was skiing over "Yastrebetz" (a racing 
track in a Bulgarian winter resort).

The doctors from Belogradchik town determined a wrong diagnosis 
to my son. A month later, after some complex examinations at ISUL 
(A medical institute in Sofia), the diagnosis was categorically rejected.

My son lives with my parents in the country and I feel this 
feeling always when leaving for Sofia, but the last time it was 
quite strong.

A colleague of mine asked a lecturer to put him a higher mark in 
order to keep his good mards and thus to continue getting a 
scholarship for an excellent grade.
I felt this feeling during the exam in higher mathematics.

My son drank four pills of diazepam every two hours instead of 
amidophen.

I am a sportwoman as well. I felt joy when after an year of 
practice, at a contest, I covered the norms for "a master of sports".

I felt fear once, when the car in which I travelled directed 
towards the precipice along the road.

When I see how people around me pass by certain unjustice because 
of indifference or cowardice.
When I left a man in whom I really believed.
Disgust with drunk people.
When I try to lie.

When I had had the possibility to act or to do certain activity 
better but I had not done it because of reluctance or 
carelessness.
When I was admitted to the University.
When I broke my leg I felt fear.
When someone lies to me.
At an unjust insult or injure.

From the cigarette smoke. Usually I feel disgust from it when I 
am in a restaurant.
When I promise to do something but I don't fulfill it.
When I don't fulfill my obligations.
When my affairs with the girl I love settled positively.

In a dam lake, when the water was let flow to water the plants 
and I and two other boys were near the water pit. We rescued 
ourselves only thanks to the flippers and the tyre that was with 
us.

It was quite recently, at the football match between the national 
teams of Bulgaria and France. I felt strong anger with the Scottish 
referee who ran the match quite partially.

When I am alone and listen to a song which I like very much and 
which I had listened before together with friends.
A striking act of ingratitude at a public vehicle.

I counterfeited a mark in the school register during the lesson 
in gymnastics. I felt this feeling two days later when I stood 
face to face with my teacher, whom I highly appreciated and 
respected.

In a fit of temper I told things that were unjust and they 
greatly hurt my mother though she didn't show it.

I passed successfully the preliminary exam for a participation in 
the children Assembly.

I was alone in my room at the boarding house when at 12 o'clock 
someone knocked violently on the door.

A friend of mine promised to come with me to the cinema but he 
didn't come.

I felt sadness when I remembered my former boyfriend with whom I 
got separated an year ago and when comparing him with my present 
one with whom things are not much of a success.

Recently in the tram, a man ran his fingers over my girlfriend 
then over me.

I had to prepare a report but I couldn't write it. I read from a 
book off-hand, I was quite uneasy and I felt I didn't manage.

My father got a slight heart attack after a telephone call of 
mine.
Bulgaria won a football match against France.
I was going to knock down a pedestrian with my car.
I was neglected undeservedly.
My grandmother died.
A man was unfair to a girlfriend of mine.
I didn't offer my seat to a pregnant woman in the bus.
I didn't attend lectures.
I felt joy when my two twin sisters were born.

The night before my wife had given birth to our twins. I felt 
fear in the hospital yard, I feared if everything was going to be 
in order.

About a month ago the Regional Council refused to pay my wife the 
due maternity benefit, because of bureaucratic reasons.

Some months ago my wife gave birth to twin sisters. She had no 
idea of looking after babies and she felt quite oppressed. The 
fact that I couldn't help her caused grief to me.

I feel disgust with some people when I see what they are capable 
of, including lack of any dignity, when trying to find a seat in 
the tram.

Some days ago I had a car accident. It was quite slight but 
through my fault. I felt strong shame because I had the spirits 
of a good driver.
Some days ago I had a slight car accident through my fault.

The period when I was pregnant and when I gave birth to my son. 
I can say those were the happiest months in my life.

A fear from the loss of a close friend as a result of his 
behavior.

When I encountered not only with my father's lack of 
understanding but also with his unwillingness to understand me as 
a parent, as far as things for which I (not he) have proves to be 
right are concerned.
From the fact that my husband and I are not in good terms.

I was disgusted from a quarrel between two married people, in 
which the children were involved as accusers of one of the 
parents.
When I don't succeed to fulfill a promise.

When I am not able to fulfill any request of my son - can't take 
him out to ride his byke, because I am tired.

I felt joy when I saw my daughter after a separation of twenty 
days.

I felt fear when I sat for one of my exams. Though my fear was 
not quite justifiable, I still remember about it.

I thought him a good friend but he tried to lie to me several times. 
Last time was the height of impudence. He promised he would come 
home but he didn't. I felt a sense of anger and insult.
A fear of lack of personal powers.

At an undeserved attitude toward a man, when human personality is 
not treated decently.
At an irrevocable loss (with respect to human relations).

At an unworthy behaviour of a man, pettiness, stupidity and 
mostly at a philistinism.
At a weakness on my part.
When I don't justify the confidence of people that I respect.
When I was admitted to the University.

Because of a conflict with my parents there was a possibility to 
interrupt my studies.
I feel a strong anger when I am treated unjustly.
At a prolonged separation with my family.

I was looking for an object when I came across a rotten corpse of 
a rat.

I feel this feeling at one and the same degree when I am not 
prepared to overcome certain obstacle in my life.

I offended a person who had done much for me and who had helped 
me for everything.
The day when my son said for the first time "mummy".
Before an exam in logics.

My husband and I were invited at the house of our nieghbours then 
we got an invitation on the part of my parents which we had to 
refuse. A a result they called me by words that provoked my 
anger.

My son lives in the country. I feel sadness when I see mothers 
having walks with their children.

The behaviour of a colleague of mine, which doesn't correspond to 
my norms of behaviour.

I was to take part in a cocktail party on the occasion of our 
national holiday as a servant.
I ignored and offended my parents on the eve of the New Year.

The sense of joy comes to me always after a period of depression, 
as an organic feeling for an upsurge. I don't exclude the 
situative feeling but in this case the reason is not in me, it's 
out of me.

I bet that I would jump down from a window. I was sure that I 
would jump but before I did it I rather felt fear.

A honest "sliding" on the part of a girlfriend of mine. 
Terribly crossed I started breaking things and tearing books.

Alone I am coming back home in the night after the serial 
"explanation".
A lie on the part of a person close to me.
I thought I had taken a decision but I hesitated.

I feel this feeling most often before me not before the others. 
My outside is iron but actually I'm wasting away.
My son was born.
I had a car accident.

I was drawn up a statement for an infringement of the traffic 
ordinance. In fact I was innocent.
I lost a close friend.

I saw a film about the nazi concentration camps during the war. 
After the film I felt disgust.

I was nailed. I lied in connection with a book which I took from 
the library, because I had to keep it for a longer time.

I didn't give back in time some money that I had borrowed. My 
friend relied on them.

After 10 days of hard work and having suffered many changes I 
passed my last exam.
Before going to the dentist.

When I am made to do things in which I see no sense and I waste 
my time. Some time ago I had to participate in a sociological 
investigation and then I got really angry.

When I feel I must be with somebody, to talk with somebody - but 
I am alone.

Some time ago a man tried to teach me something. "Tried" because 
it is very difficult to teach somebody when you yourself are not 
competent and cultured.

I am ashamed when I am not ready for my seminar in internal 
diseases, simply because the assistant professor is a person who 
deserves high respect.

We had promised, with a friend of mine, to take our friends to a 
restaurant and after having looked for a place for hours without 
finding one, and not being helped by the others we had to give up 
the idea.

When I am with friends and I do what pleases me this often 
happenes.

When I have to go in for an exam and the examinor is a person 
with a whimsical character and unsteady requirements.

I unfairly got a low mark on an exam and I failed to win a grant, 
since then I don't have much confidence in myself at an exam.
It happened that I was alone - with no contacts with friends.

I met three drunk boys, almost children, they didn't look like 
normal people.

I was totally unprepared for a seminar conducted by an assistant 
professor whom I highly respect.

I got back too late after a Sunday going out without having 
called up home to tell where I was. my mother hadn't slept the 
whole night.

I was happy when I understood that the girl I liked was in love 
with me.
I am afraid before an exam or colloquium.

I get angry when my smaller brother misbehaves and talks with indecent 
words.
When my dog was stolen.

I detest any kind of constraint and hate the attempts of elder 
people to force me to a norm of behavior without having legal or 
moral rights to do it. I felt this emotion when a neighbour of 
mine made me kick out my guests because they had talked very 
loudly and threatened that with "connections" she will expel me 
from the inst.

I experienced long ago when I was sightseeing Bulgarians in a 
foreign language.

My mother developed hipertonia and I think I too am to blame 
bacause with her it is a stress disease.
When I met with friends that I hadn't seen for a long time.

One evening a friend of mine was telling a fearful story, nobody 
took it seriously but I got frightened.

I got angry with a stranger in a train who behaved impertinently 
and immorally
When I failed at the first entrance exam.
The event which got me angry got also an aversion in me.
Once I was not ready for a seminar and I was asked to leave.
I felt guilty when once I made my mother angry.

Six months ago when I got acquaintanced with a person whom I 
trusted infinitely and from whom I expected help and friendly 
feelings. With him I found much in common - in our views and in 
our fate.

Few days ago I really experienced fear. It was connected with 
unexpected actions on the part of a group of people. This evoked 
in me many negative emotions.

I always get angry when somebody deceives me, or tries to conceal 
his lie skilfully and this offends me even more.

Sadness - this is an emotion which I have felt very often 
recently. I can't remember a concrete example. I will describe my 
general impression from severl situations which evoked this 
feeling in me.

I became disgusted with the man on whom I had counted, who I had 
trusted, the man who should have been my mainstay - my father. 
I could hardly make myself (and the others) believe in this 
emotion. It has cumulated after events and deeds. Everything can 
happen in this world.

I am ashamed of the way my father behaves with my mother and 
sister, and with me too.

I didn't keep a promise I had made to a man, and in this way I 
lost his esteem and confidence in me. I caused him a lot of 
trouble.
When I was accepted as a student.

I was a bit frightened when it was found that there was something 
wrong with my liver. However it turned out that it was not 
serious and I need not worry.

With the girl whom I may be loved truly. When she refused to come 
with me to an occasion (she was from another town).

For the girl who halped me go on living and made me happy - when 
I don't see her even for two or three days.

For a drunk man (about 20 years old) that I met one evening, and 
who behaved impudently with the girls standing by.

I was embarassed at the exam in microbiology. I was ashamed with 
myself - how little I knew and how good was the examinor. I 
rarely become ashamed.

Recently when I made a slip and blurted out indecent words in my 
mother's presence.

I felt it when on duty in the hospital I understood that I was 
not afraid to face death, that I also helped a little to relieve 
the pains of a patient.

Fear overwhelmed me when right against the car I was in I saw 
another one, as if out of control of the driver.

I felt it when a girl who was dear to me lied to my face. I got 
angry with the fact that she knew I didn't believe her but she 
kept on telling lies.
Sadness, no, I felt something much stronger when my father died.

I got disgusted with a man who was beating a woman in the street. 
I just happened to be there but I was abhorred by the rudness.

I was ashamed of the way I deceived that I could not help a 
friend, although it was absolutely possible for me. Nothing was 
revealed but I haven't called up this person since then.

I had an appointment with a colleague of mine to give her my 
lecture notes. I couldn't go and I didn't send them, and so the 
girl missed a day for the preparation of her term exams.
When I knew that my husband and I were going to have a child.

Two years ago I saw a film on the TV. Even now it makes me 
afraid.
When my husband stays late at a meeting and I have to be alone.
The loss of a person I loved very much.
Deception from a person I loved very much.

I didn't tell my parents that I was going to Sofia. I told them 
that I was going to a seminar. My mother knew that I was lying but 
she didn't stop me.

The assistant professor saw me cheat at the preliminary 
examination.

I was very happy when I got the message that I had been accepted 
as a student in medicine.

I felt something close to that when I saw that there was a man on 
the terrace of the flat.

I got angry when I learned how short a time we had to prepare for 
the term examinations.

I felt sad when my first boyfriend and I left each other. It was neither 
his fault nor mine.

I felt it today when the bus driver shouted rather indecent words 
at a man without any reason whatsoever.

At an exam in pharmacology I tried to prompt a coleague (she 
asked me something) and the assistant professor made me a sharp 
remark.

My grandmother has been in a hospital for a week and I still 
haven't had time to see her.

When I learned that my parents were going abroad and leaving me 
alone for a few years.

I was at the seaside and my brother disappeared for a couple of 
hours.

Some time ago I was disgusted with the "cleanness" of the 
refectory of our institute.

We were at a football match and when we were leaving the stadium 
(the stadium was packed with people) and I lost my shoe in the 
crowd. Our attempts to find it didn't give any result and I had 
to go home without one shoe. In other words to cross the whole 
town !

I felt guilty last year during the winter term exams. A colleague 
of mine asked me to give him my lecture notes (I had very good 
notes and I had passed my exam in advance) but I still don't know 
why I didn't give them to him. That colleague failed and he was 
on the verge of not passing it at the supplementary examinations.

When I was admitted to the Institute. I had problems with many 
people about my applying for this institute and I decided to 
prove that one can pass excellently without visiting any 
preparatory couse. That is - I proved what I could do on my own.

Once as a child I dreamed of a fire. Since that time I hadn't 
wanted to sleep in that bed and had feared the night darkness 
(and so it is now).

A chief was unjustly punished on an autumn brigade and the one 
who was really guilty kept silent. I stepped in front and told 
the truth. The guilty chief called me in after the roll-call and 
threatened me.

Years ago I fell in love for the first time. as natural for every 
school-girl I was day-dreaming. Later (after 3 years) we left 
each other. No one was to blame but I felt deep sadness. Even now 
I remember about it quite often.

It was at a comsomol(??) meeting, the last one because we were to 
graduate. The way one of my fellow-students behaved made me feel 
disgusted.

I was at a children's camp abroad. The people (the leaders, my 
coevals) were very king to us. One night we smeared our foreign 
friends with tooth-paste while they were sleeping and then we 
roused the whole camp by our shouts. Later I was so sorry. I 
didn't utter a word for two days, then I went to apologize.

When I was in the fifth class the rating was done in our 
mark-books. I hadn't been examined yet but I had heard from my 
classmates about the scolding they had got at home. My first 
mark was in geography - good 4. I judged I had known for more 
than that and I put down "very good" for fear of being scolded. 
Naturally my parents guessed all about it. They rebuked me for 
what I had done.

When I learned I was admitted to study what I wanted most - 
floriculture (this is a narrow specialization from the general 
one).

I was walking on the pavement when a white car rolled on it and 
directed towards me. I was quite near the house wall when it 
rolled by and hit me.

My grandmother's brother had taken active part in the resistance 
movement. He had been in prison many times and there he lost his 
health. He became an invalid. When we phoned to First Aid the 
nurse on duty behaved quite unkindly when she understood how old 
he was (79).

My boyfriend is a soldier. He was on a leave. I felt sad when we 
had to get separated again.

I felt disgusted about a teacher who had rejected all that was 
human in her. She refused to accept the flowers we gave her for 
the eighth of March and asked for a foreign parfume instead.

I was examined by a teacher I greatly respected. I was well 
prepared on the subjects but he put some side-issues to me and I 
couldn't answer.

I had undertaken to help my sister for her class work but some 
unexpected circumstances prevented me from doing that.

I was very glad when I learned I was a student already. I heard 
about it over the phone, I didn't believe it at first.
I had worries about a certain illness.

I suffered from a gynaecological illness. I was quite displeased 
to hear that my roommates had talked about it and they had 
misrepresented the truth. I felt deeply hurt when I learned that 
it was done by a "good" acquaintance of mine.

When my first boyfriend left me. I tried not to let him 
understand I felt miserable.

I hate hypocrisy. My friend (girl) tried to intrude into my 
affairs with my future husband. After that she behaved as if 
nothing had happened.

I feel shame when I have made a promise, I can't keep it and this 
has negative effects which are caused by my behavior.

I felt it when I came home after the examination session and I 
said I had not passed my last exam.

I felt glad when I took the rather difficult organic chemistry 
examination.

This was what I felt when my boyfriend went to Bourgas to study 
there. I had the feeling I would lose him. Anyway the distance 
Plovdiv-Bourgas seemed to me so great.

I confronted with this feeling at the Institute quite recently, 
the pedology lecturer was the cause.

This feeling was quite deep when my friend (girl) died in a car 
accident.

I am disgusted with the behavior of a car driver whose car would 
run over me and my friends during our autumn brigade.
I felt shame when I discontinued my education for eight months.

The sense of guilt came over me too, when I interrupted my 
studies. Why ? Because I felt guilty before my parents ! They 
believed in me though this event did not make them disbelieve me.

I sensed a strong feeling of joy when in the plant, at my working 
place, I got a message that I was admitted as full time student at 
the Higher Agricultural Institute.

Fear when fulfilling my obligations on my first night fatigue 
duty as a soldier.

When on a car journey a fellow student crossed our way with his 
own car and we had to bump into a roadside trunk.
The loss of a close relative who was ill with cancer.

I am disgusted with a nieghbour who is looking for all sorts of 
quarrel with my parents and me. He feels we are hampering his 
living close to us. This has been going on for quite a long time.

Some time ago I promised to meet an acquaintance of mine and to 
carry him some promised papers. I haven't done it until this day. 
Now I feel quite awkward when I meet him.

A sense of guilt before my parents when I had to discountinue my 
studies in the first year because of unpassed exams.

After a difficult exam. When I had not hoped to take it and had 
got a high mark. When you present someone with something and he 
feels glad.

Fear from the unknown. I felt fear when I sat for the entrance 
examinations.

I feel angry at people's indifference at our ability to be 
present at an event and to stay partial to what happens.

When you are far away from relatives and friends. I feel sad for 
my early years, for the freedom and the carefree years of 
childhood.
I feel disgusted with the bootlickers, with helpless people.
I feel ashamed when I act dishonestly toward somebody.

I didn't visit a very close friend at the hospital and some days 
later he died.

I was sitting for an exam in biochemistry, I was very excited 
because it was a supplementary examination. I passed the exam 
very well and was glad because I recovered my selfconfidence.

Students fear many things but we seem to fear the examinations 
most of all. I remember I was horror stricken before my 
microbiology exam, because it was a decisive one.

It was necessary to organise a competition in connection with a 
celebration. Everyone was to be present at that event. It turned 
out that there was no audience at all because everyone had 
pretended to be very intelligent and no one had come. I got 
furious.

When I part with my friends I feel always sad for some time. I 
can't remember a concrete example now. For example I have just 
parted with a friend of mine and I am feeling sad.

In autumn I had to move to another lodging. My landlords, quite 
intelligent people, warned me I had to move in the nearest 
future. But I had difficulties in moving my luggage because I 
couldn't wait for a car to come. How amazed I was to hear them 
threatening me they would throw our my things. And at that my 
luggage was well packed and did not stand in their way. I was 
quite  disappointed and disgusted.

During our last exarcise in agricultural machines we went out in 
the yard to examine a row of machines. But we seemed not to have 
fulfilled our task well, because when our teacher came and asked 
me a question I was unable to answer. I felt awkward because he 
didn't deserve it.

I remember about an unpleasant event in relation to my mother. I 
felt guilty before her.

When I succeded in establishing a contact with a girl (who is now 
my girlfriend).
I fear before each exam.
When my bosom friend tried to lie to me.
When I quarrelled with a very close friend of mine.
When I see the acts and deeds of a blind drunk man.

When I wasn't well prepared for a terminal exam and the teacher 
tried to give me a three by asking me some very easy questions. I 
burned with shame then.

When once my mother asked me to do some work for her at home 
because she was busy and moreover this work was to be done by a 
man. But it remained undone.

I feel joy usually after each taken exam, the last one was in 
February.

It was not long ago when I and two of friends of mine got quite drunk 
and one of them began to rave under the influence of the alcohol. 
I felt fear of what could have happened.

I felt anger at my last exam, I felt angry with our teacher, 
because he did not rate me objectively and I failed.

I met a girl some time ago and I cared very much about her but it 
happened so that we left each other. I felt some sort of sadness, I think 
I can call it so.

I had a very good friend (boy) and I thought I could rely on him 
but he behaved badly with a girl who used to trust us completely.

Immediately after the New Year holidays I happened to visit a 
party where there was a lot of alcohol and I became drunk. On the 
next day I felt sort of ashamed when I remembered what I had said 
and done on the night before.

Last year I put off an exam for the autumn session without 
knowing if there was a supplementary examination session. When I 
came home with my exam unpassed I felt guilty before my parents 
when I remembered how much they had done for me.
When I was admitted to the Higher Institute.

I felt fear when I fell down and broke my leg into pieces and I 
could not feel it at all.

I felt angry when I failed in an exam about which I knew quite a 
few things and I did not deserve to be plucked.

When my mother and father were on an excursion in Chechoslovakia 
and I was at a student camp and I heard over the radio about the 
events that were taking place there.

I felt disgust with alcohol in general when a close friend of 
mine got so drunk that he didn't realize what he was doing and it 
was quite shameful.

I felt ashamed when my parents found out that I had deceived 
them.

I felt guilty when I had taken the car keys and I had an accident 
but as my parents did not know who was to blame, they punished my 
brother because I had no driving licence and they thought it 
impossible that had driven the car.

I felt joy when I was admitted to the Higher Agricultural 
Institute.

I feel fear quite often but this feeling was very strong last 
year when my husband was quite unexpectedly sent to the hospital.

That was what I felt with a teacher who put down quite unreal 
marks.

I felt sad when a friend of mine died and I felt that something 
had irrevocably gone away from me.

I felt disgust with a lady teacher who used to nag, to mock, to 
interrupt everyone of my fellow students each time we had a class 
with her in our first year.

That was what I felt when I told my first lie and then was 
cought.

I felt guilty when I failed to take an exam though I had had 
enough time to read for it but I hadn't made use of it.

I was for the first time on a brigade this year. At that time my 
sister was to bear a child. I was mad with joy when I opened the 
telegram from my parents and learned I had a nephew.

It was some years ago when one evening some people came home and 
told us my father was badly injured in an accident.

I faced this feeling when I realized I wasn't admitted to the 
institute in the first classifying, in spite of the high mark I 
had got at the entrance examination.

Always when I get separated from my friends and relatives from my 
home town.

I feel disgust with my first boyfriend who made fun of our love 
in an abominable way.

I have always felt ashamed for some people's behavior to their 
too old parents. I have felt hurt and shy when they have left 
them to the mercy of fate.

I feel always guilty before my parents when I come home and have 
to tell them I have failed an exam.

Naturally when I got myself discharged this was my second 
birthday.
When I failed my first exam at the Higher Institute.

A nuisance used to live in our flat a month ago. I experienced 
this feeling when I tried to chase her out.
After my father's death.
With an alcoholic.

Once I had dinner at an elegant restaurant and I did not have 
enough money to pay the bill. There were a lot of people there 
and I felt quite awkward.

Something very unpleasant happened when I was a soldier and I was 
directly involved in it.

I felt the greatest burst of joy when after being heavily ill for 
a long period, my father came back home.

I was terrified during an axcursion in Italy. I was lost and left 
alone in this unfamiliar country.

I took part in a football match. The referee was extremely 
partial to the opposite team. This stirred up my discontent and 
anger.
When my first girlfriend an I left each other.

During a summer holiday at a bar I happened to see a dead to the 
world woman.
When I first had a sexual intercourse.

I remember when I was a little boy I broke a Swiss dinner set 
quite involuntarily.

When I got a message that I was employed as a nurse at a 
kindergarten.
When I first sat for an entrance examination.

When a teacher though pretending to be a highly cultivated 
teacher and a man, slapped a classmate of mine in the face quite 
undeservedly.
When I got separated from my first love.

Many times, when my father used to come home drunk and maltreated 
physically me and my mother.

When for the first and the last time I tried to crib and the 
teacher was with her back to me but right when I was taking the 
materials out she turned round and saw me.

When at times unconscienciously I speak to my mother in a high 
tome but after that I am sorry and I feel guilty.

Being invited out by a person I wished to get closer to. He 
telephoned and invited me to go out with him the next night.
Watching a horror movie with friends.

The breakup of a relationship. After the event I was upset/sad 
then angry maybe 2/3 weeks later.

The funeral of a friend who was killed in a car accident. She was 
of my own age, there were many of my own friends present, as well 
as her family etc.

Disgust for a person who treated me badly, and has treated other 
people similarly - including lying, hiding facts, being 
deceitful, unfair, etc.

Losing my temper and allowing myself to act childishly by yelling 
and screaming at a person who I felt had done me wrong - in 
effect lowering myself to their level.

Guilt at often being unable to visit a close relative in hospital 
after her death I felt very guilty and wished I had done more.

Achievement of a task by a friend who had begun a new job. She 
wasn't confident of handling the situation so was thinking  of 
leaving the job only after 2 days employment.

Walking home at night after university - part of the way, there 
are ano lights and I am walking down a thoroughfare with the 
thouth of no one hearing me if I have to scream.

When my son omits to carry out certain duties at home that he 
knows needs doing.

When I saw my niece (5 yrs) crying in the hallway for her mother 
who had passed away about a month ago.

With a woman who had walked into my place of employment and 
urinated on the floor in front of everyone.

When I found a letter addressed "To Mum" by my son, 6 months 
later, he begged me not to sell his new shoes which he messed up 
after wearing them for the first time.

When I had lied to a friend/son about some things we had 
discussed and I had to be one better.

Felt joy a few years ago when I was away on holiday. And sat very 
close to my best friend looking straight into the eyes.

I had to tell someone that I was interested in remaining celibate 
and alone. And that my spiritual master strictly prohibited 
sexual relations outside of marriage. This caused great fear 
through lack of conviction afraid to hurt someone's feelings 
despite my own being hurt in the process.

In a sociology class I felt very angry towards some members of 
society for exploiting the Polynesian people, dawn raids by 
Police (Martin Luther King, Blacks in S.A.). But this was just a 
reflection of my own shortcomings.

Felt sad about some street kids in QUEII square, Aotea square. 
Because they had been sniffing glue and some were very young. I 
went into the role of a performing clown.

I was disgusted by my paranoid attitude towards myself, my 
homework at university and disgusted about my lack of retention. 
Especially in learning another language.

I felt shame at the hurt I caused to my family especially my 
parent father, shame of hurting people emotionally. A misconceived 
self-blaming that didn't do me any good. Shame at being myself as 
I am.

I felt guilty at being part of the successful people. Felt guilty 
at being a student when other people were not. Guilt about being 
a potential success in various areas of society. (So stupid this 
emotion)

When I meet old past pupils of mine - and find they are all doing 
well - I feel joy. Yesterday I met a young woman (20 yrs) I'd 
taught her at 6 yrs, then at 12 yrs and hadn't seen her for last 
3-4 yrs; she was no longer a waitress but a meter maid for 
Council.

A Maori language oral test, yeaterday - Although I had studied 
intensely - once in the examiners room "I blew it" -  I was so 
nervous I couldn't reply easily - It was very important, but I 
got only blankness.

A friend visited and made comments that my house/garden were not 
as neat/tidy as in the past. I'd not seen her a year - She 
implied I'd gone to the pack (I'd only been working full time, 
and taking 3 University exams part time).

When my father a 4th/5th generation colonial (from Eng.) attacked 
me verbally about my chosen partner. A man whom he discarded 
because his colour skin was not white. His ultimate disgust 
saddned me.

People who came to our home - and requested "Put out your smoke". 
That we should not smoke in our house... and asked not even 
politely. It disgusted me because I think people need to adapt to 
the situation.

Put down by my father - at a family outing at mutual family 
friends dinner. Told "Not to Speak". The attitude by him was 
negative/I was in mid 20s, I had done many things - a wide range 
of experiences. Probably greater than he.

Not attending school, when  am not sick - but in need of mental 
rest. Staff on your return query your "sickness" - it is easier 
in N.Z. to be sick, rather than confide other personal reasons 
etc.
My 3 children - each top his class in the final exams 1984.

A truck (big one) nearly mowed me off the road (I was driving a 
small Lazer).

A shop in Downtown wouldn't accept my Visa Card - before December 
last year.

My dog of 16 and 1/2 years - "Lord Grey" died in his sleep - His 
death caused me more and deeper sadness than I thought.
A sour looking man was beating his thin dog in Remuera.

I told Mr Winter of Downtown Fashion to go to - when he did not 
accept my Visa !
When I accepted a lunch invitation from a past male friend.
When my daughter was born.

When my mother entered surgery for a quadruple heart bypass. I 
felt intense fear at the time she was actually wheeled away.

When my husband got picked up in our new car for drunken driving. 
We had made a pact the other would not drink and so therefore 
would be the driver for the evening etc. I was not present at the 
time.
When my grandmother died very suddenly without warning.

When the N.Z. rugby union announced that they would proceed with 
a rugby tour of South Africa.

When I was unable to respond to a welcome in my indigenous 
language of Maori at an important function where I was the only 
woman in the group and it was expected of me.

When I made an excuse to get out of participating in an important 
family occasion that I should not have missed.

Being reunited with my family after not having seen them for 5 
years, at the airport. Sheer elation at getting through the 
"paper work" collecting bags and the anticipation of coming 
through the customs gate.

I caught a huge eel on a fishing line which I had pulled into the 
boat. I cut the line and threw the whole lot back into the water. 
Later that day and about ten miles away I went swimming and 
someone made the comment wondering how far eels could swim, I 
abruptly ended swimming for fear at an unseen eel for a few days 
until we had left the district.

My partner without discussing with me the situation decided it 
was time for us to have a break and went ahead and arranged his 
own life for the next 6-12 months, then told me the day before it 
was about to happen having been tolerant and friendly for the 
preceding week.

I had been living in an overseas city and made the decision to 
leave the city and come home about 12 months before I met a whole 
new set of friends, leaving them at the airport was sad and 
traumatic as they had helped me in many ways and I knew I 
wouldn't see many of them again.

After I had managed to fail my first year at University I was 
scared as to what I was going to do with my future. I didn't want 
a mundane 9-5 job and yet I didn't know if I could pay my way 
through an unsubsidized year at university to settle down and 
continue my studies.

This situation keeps occurring - when my little sister disagrees 
with me or vice-versa. We have very similar temperaments and I 
always end up feeling angry at her and myself for fighting so 
much over unimportant trivial matters.

When my grandmother, who has been living with us for 14 years, 
had a stroke and was left paralysed on one side. She has been 
quite close to our family and to see her suffer in this way makes 
me feel really sad.

A gathering of a social sports club at which they proceeded to 
show pornographic videos and then afterwards (when most people 
had had quite a bit to drink) carried on in a very degrading, 
unmoral manner - especially females exposing and flaunting 
themselves with no shame or embarassment.

Like guilt - the most ashamed I have ever felt was when I began 
to feel guilty about having sex with my boyfriend when it was 
only "the thing to do", and not really an act of love.

This feeling of guilt really applies to moral/religious views. I 
(being Catholic) went against what I was brought up to believe in 
and had a sexual relationship with my boyfriend. Many months 
later, when I was doing some deeper self analysis I began to feel 
guilty and realized that I had gone against what I wanted for 
myself and my future.

My mother along with some of my friends gave me a surprise 
birthday party - they invited a large number of my friends along 
too.

My mother did not come home till late at night (Ages ago). Anyway 
if I don't know where my parents are and when they'll be back I 
start thinking that perhaps they have had an accident and are 
perhaps dead.

Because I am the Captain of a basketball team I usually organise 
a roster system so that everyone in the team can have a turn at 
doing either a duty or a ref. A lot of the time the girls can't 
be bothered or just forget - I usually have to fill in.

So as to be closer to the university I have left home and moved 
into Auckland. It now seems as if I have left home - especially 
my family - forever.

A friend of mine goes out with this guy. She sleeps with him but 
is quite happy for him to play around - as well as herself.
NO RESPONSE.

I did not attend a social studies observation class for 1 whole 
week (I am a student trainee teacher). Anyway the other teachers 
thought this was okay because the teacher I was supposed to 
observe was not well liked. The teacher was in fact really nice 
to me - but I wanted to get out of teaching a hard topic he had 
given me.

Passing my pharmacy exams which meant my tertiary education for 
pharmacy completed.

When I was in a car with my parents and friends and we had to 
back up (reverse) pass a river which when I recall it (I was only 
about 5 yrs) seemed we were going to fall in and drown.

When my boyfriend wouldn't dance with me on my graduation night 
because he thought I could dance with my friends who were 
friendly.

When my sister (really my niece) died of cancer at the age of 2 
yrs after I took her to the doctor at the age of 1 and he 
diagnosed it.

My brother gave me a beating because he could not beat me 
verbally.
I found I was pregnant and unmarried.

When I had to go to reconciliation before converting to 
Catholicism but then once received - o.k.

Joy for me is when all my family gather around home for special 
occasions as Christmas etc. It really gives me joy to see my 
family and relatives and to observe natures productivity process 
which have been going on for centuries.

I had this experience of fear when few people were fighting at a 
social one night, which one of my relative was involved. My fear 
was greatly for him because he was being assaulted badly.
Never really had the experience just yet - N/A.

This occurred when my girlfriend and I have to finish our 
relationship due to some circumstances between her and her 
family. I was really sad, hurt and couldn't really find any 
reason why am I still living. Is this life is all about ? This 
was one of few question which crept up vividly every time I 
thought about what had happened.

I'm very disgusted when I see people abusing their body with 
drugs and alcohol. They take advantage of these things usually 
for an excuse for the fantasies which they like and so they do 
things stupidly and unjustly.
NO RESPONSE.
This I experienced when going around with more than one girl.
Letting Jesus take control of my emotions i.e., ill feeling.
Had fear of losing husband.

When present boyfriend's mother approached my parents and self - 
to leave her son alone - as she did not want me for a future 
daughter-in-law.
When boyfriend could not stand up to his mother or for himself.

Disgusted with boyfriend's mother - her overpowering,

That if ever I was really naughty I would be sent away from my

(1) My father died. (2) My natural father contacted me a year

My father died. I was away at the time and did not know until two

When my natural parents name would show up on papers and not my,

I lied to my mother in the sixth form she said she would ring to

When approached by a gang of youths in town at night.

My anger is with men, their inability to be human (not all men).

The saddest I've ever been was when my lover was killed,

With the N.Z. Rugby Union wanting to send the All Blacks to South

That my brother and father are into alcohol, two men with

I walked up the main street of Auckland at 10 o'clock at night. I

Someone in my family (my brother I suspected) ate a bun which I

Sitting in a bus, I heard behind, the voice of a girl I was

Having moved into a flat within the last week I felt some disgust

I criticised an action of my mother and for the first time she

I felt that I contributed to a possible rift in the relationship

My friend replying to my letter and again saying he was attracted

Being sexually assaulted (not rape, but passionate kissing) by a

When my grandmother died - I wasn't sad so much that she'd died

When during a social evening with my father, brother, sister,

When the girl whom I have lusted after expressed reciprocal

While intoxicated I invaded someone's (a girl's) personal space

While intoxicated I damaged my sister's car in a minor way and

Girlfriend arriving back from overseas and picking her up from

Fear of punishment for having broken an item of value to my

That a friend had been badly beaten and stabbed many times and

The death of an animal we had reared.

Finding that a girlfriend of mine was a prostitute and had been

Not having owned up to the responsibility an incident where

Had started a relationship and did nothing to keep it up, partly

The feeling of joy when again I had confessed my sin and

Riding through a bush fire on an island of Australia - on a

When someone I had had a relationship (purely sexual) with came

When a close friend entrusted me with a secret and I let the cat

Making a sexual pass at my cousin with whom I have a very close

First time I slept with my present girlfriend. Had been best

Waiting for a taxi - when within 1/2 an hour two separate people

Deliberately provoked by someone close. Angered by the

My girlfriend let me down badly 3 times in one week. These

A close friend took part in a racist violent action.
Cannot recall the emotion with any force.
Slept with someone close to my girlfriend and myself.

Hearing that I had been successful in getting a position whereby

When I decided to leave my steady, secure employment to come to

When a close friend failed to live up to the expectations I had

Departure of a very close friend - for a long stay overseas,

I get disgusted with the inherent racist attitudes of my

My failure to provide the appropriate emotional/spiritual level

When I deliberately engineered a situation to cause tension

Hearing Fran Wilde introduce the Bill.

Being harrassed for being gay; suggestions of being physically

Hearing Norman Jones get hysterical in Parliament about law

Watching Muldoon act as my P.M.

Adolescent guilt growing up feeling "bad, immoral" sexual

Won a prize for effort.
Assaulted by drunken neighbour.

I was playing in a football tournament and saw the rules openly

Death of brother.
Reading literature on AIDS/homosexuality.

I am ashamed at myself sometimes when I am working with

I was late meeting someone for an appointment.

I was feeling really low - had been a series of fights with my

I was watching a movie alone - it was a horror movie. The music

My sister and I were fighting as usual. She's older tham I am,

My paternal grandmother had died. We weren't close but she was

My older sister used to pick on my brothers and sisters all of

My first real experience with a boy. We were alone. I was quite

I was using my sister's stereo while everyone was out. I know she

Winning a rowing race at a Karapiro regatta. With 7 other

Being alone in Europe and having to catch a train and bus to the

At school teacher for not allowing us to go out on New Year's Eve

I was in a car accident on the way back from a weekend rowing

Our boarder burping after meals !

Felt ashamed when in a group conversation and could not

Guilty when I hadn't walked my dog for quite a few days and had

When I won a position on the track-team for the trans-tasman

When I was jumped by three men in a deserted area.

When my mother died.

When somebody who had been a bully and had acted cruelly to

When I was twelve I was babysitting some children but I did not

When something went wrong for me I lashed out at someone else

Easter holiday - I had been working weekends and had just left.
Haven't been frightened for ages.

I felt sad with the two situations I described before. The cat

Next door nieghbour ran over his cat in driveway, he tried to

Haven't felt shame for ages.

I borrowed a friend's books and forgot I had them, she asked for

Getting my kitten, found at work several years ago, taking him

At work being shifted to another area.

Enrolling at varsity, being told I couldn't get in to certain

Noticing my flat had maggotts !

At my wedding - standing with the man I love and acknowledging

As a result of breaking the indicator light as mentioned

At the death of my husband's father's mother which occurred

With a Manager who insists on making crude innuendos pertaining

Breaking the left hand indicator box by moving too close to

Waking in morning (early morning) and having whole day to myself.

Being driven by friend who suddenly swerved and skidded a little.

Friend (male) hinted that my talking to other men at a pub was

On rising. No apparent reason.

Prolonged "niggling" of friend on a single theme which I

Felt I had not appreciated my parents enough. Regretted the

Boyfriend doing cleaning in situation where it was my job to do

When my first niece was born.

In a flat in Sydney - rough area at home on my own - the flat had

When the bus driver failed to stop and pick me up at a bus stop.

Watching an alcoholic woman who was approaching everyone at the

Two timing - going out with 2 guys at once (secretly).

When I went to the pub with a large group of friends, we drank

Watched a horror movie which involved sexual attacks on women.

My boyfriend promised to take me to see a game of tennis and rang

I was driving along and saw this young guy urinating into the

Birth of children.
Being alone at night.
In a hurry to get to lectures and the car would not start.

Obscene phone calls.

Being with a close friend, in the city, who was involved at the

Telling white lies.
Thought had discovered true love.

Stopped at lights in Mangere late one Friday night on way home

Close friend leave to go overseas for an indefinite period.

When employer made a pass at me whilst I was at work.

When caught shoplifting and the police were called in parents

When caught shop-lifting as for shame.

Receiving understanding from within self of a subject I had

To talk in a meeting - expound my thoughts on a subject. Fear

Towards wife's laziness in not performing her usual duties

Watching suffering in Third World country.

Observation of people lost in the profit motive - i.e. business

On own reading book. Recall came to mind of slight sexual

Telling a lie to wife over phone about what I had been working

Meeting best friend at the airport (boyfriend) who I had missed

Confronted outside a party by some very nasty character -

NO RESPONSE.
My cat died painfully and slowly.

Having unwanted attention paid to me in my place of work -

Close friend discovered I had deceived them. Felt shame at having

Two-timing - going out with person other than guy I was in

I was very pleased and happy when my older sister came home from

I was skiing alone and the mountain became covered with mist and

My parents didn't allow me to go to a social function that all my

While still at school a friend died of cancer, after being ill

At a party my best girlfriend got really drunk and went off with

I was severely reprimanded for a trivial offence in front of

Someone asked me to do something and I made up an excuse and said

When my brother who has been out of New Zealand for 10 years came

When I had to give a speech about some historical event, to an

In arguments with a close friend or relative where my point of

When my grandfather whom I had met only once for 3 weeks, died

I once saw a programme on TV describing how certain wild life

The 2nd time someone I had met cared for came over to my house I

The first time I went away with my boyfriend and lied about where

When my former boyfriend and I reconciled and he decided that I

When riding in a very fastly-driven car on a lose metal road at a

When at very short notice I agreed to work in place of a friend

When I learned that my former boyfriend had become engaged -

When reading a newspaper story of a man who had committed

When dropping a carton of boiling soup onto a co-worker's leg -

When my sister had the opportunity to do some modelling work. And

I did a solo flight from Ardmore to Kaikohe before I got my pilot

A friend (female) and I were on holiday on Great Barrier Island

I "cooked" the engine in my father's car - it was actually his

When I finally got home I was absolutely screamed at and the

This sounds really predictable and usual but it was absolutely

I once saw an old man up the road, fossicking through the rubbish

When I was 15 my mother discovered various items in my room which

NO RESPONSE.

A holiday at a whitesand deserted beach. A cool evening near the

Skiing down a very icy slope, very fast in white-out conditions.

My best friend at school told lies about me to a boy I was seeing

I found a baby opposum on the road and took it home and cared for

A boyfriend with whom I split up with came over to a friend's

I told my primary teacher I hadn't done my homework as my mother

I told my pesent boyfriend that I was an Australian as are my

He eventually found out when told in front of me by my mother.

Winning a race that I had been training for, for many weeks.

When I was very young and we moved as a family to Auckland from

When someone ignores what I am saying or doesn't let me have my

When I got into an argument with someone and was very abusive,

When a close relative got quite drunk. It was a relative that I

When I had come home drunk the day after a party, I felt very

When I crashed by bike into an old lady crossing a road and

Listening to the opening bars of Tchaikovsdy's symphony No.2

As a passenger in a vehicle travelling from the steep side of

As in sadness (A), relating to this slaghter of fur-seals.

A) A documentary in which baby fur seals were being

B) Description of a disfigured orphaned child in Hiroshima

The repression of rioting and non-rioting "Blacks" in South

Breaking an implicit promise.

At the age of 12 (or so) I stole from a Ranger's fruit tree an

Seeing my sister after about 2 years of not seeing her. Only

I imagined I heard footsteps up the hall while sleeping in bed

Stopped at a Fast Food shop with friends and a few locals wanted

My flatmate and close friend living and sleeping with another

Sleeping with a girl on a Saturday night and then not contacting

Stealing money from a milk token jar from a close friend of the

Talking with someone I admire a lot.
Held under water by a large wave and thought I was drowning.

Came back from surfing to find car broken into and gear and money

Caused a family disturbance.
Friends calling me fat - pear shaped in front of a nice girl.
When I considered writing a load of crap for this emotion.
Beating my brother up.
I was "best man" at my brother's wedding a year ago.
Mugged while on holiday in the U.S.A.

I am one of four directors of a company. We inherited land held

Social situation - at the pub - a close friend of 2 years told

A drunk walked out in front of a car at night. Both lower legs

My father died 4 years ago, 18 months after my mother died. I

My grandmother wanted me to help her. I was driving a tractor

Hearing my girlfriend accept my offer of marriage.
Canoeing across harbour in winds - 20 knots and rising seas.

Brother continually interupting while I was talking on the

Hearing of the death of a friend who had been skiing.

Flicking through a magazine showing pictures of homosexual men

Being caught by parents in a compromising situation with
